#import "/formatting.typ": *

#show: recipe.with(title: "Sourdough Pizza", description: [

  This is a thick, chewy sourdough pizza. See the original recipe
  here:~https://www.thedivinechef.com/post/quick-sourdough-pizza.

  *Warning:* This recipe is a @adv_hydration[high-hydration] recipe. Attempt at your own
  peril.
])[
  Dough:
  - 240 grams (1 cup), active sourdough starter (100% hydration)
  - 170 grams (3/4 cup), warm water
  - 40 grams (3 tbsp.) olive oil
  - 275 grams (2 1/2 cups), bread flour#footnote[~While you _can_ use all-purpose flour,
      it will not work well, because this recipe is very chewy.]
  - 5 grams (1 tsp.) salt


  Recommended toppings:
  - Tomato sauce
  - Shredded mozarrella
  - Pickled green olives
  - Turkey pepperoni

  *Yields 1 pizza.*
]

+ MIX: wet ingredients (incl. starter); dry ingredients.
+ COVER bowl with damp towel.
+ REST. #pause[12-24 hr.]
+ PREHEAT oven, 230°C. #aside[450°F]
+ WHALLOP crust into baking sheet.
+ BAKE. #pause[20-25 min.]
+ REMOVE from sheet.
+ ADD water to sheet.
+ REINSERT crust, upside-down.
+ ADD toppings.
+ BAKE. #pause[7-10 min.]
+ REMOVE from oven.
+ REST. #pause[\~5 min.]
+ SLICE as desired.
